title: Cape Girardeau man shot to death in West End neighborhood
text:
Law and order Close 
Police investigate a fatal shooting on Thursday, Feb. 9, 2017, in the 5500 block of Cates Avenue. Photo by Nassim Benchaabane Cape Girardeau man shot to death in West End neighborhood 6 hrs ago ( … ) 
Police investigate a fatal shooting on Thursday, Feb. 9, 2017, in the 5500 block of Cates Avenue. Photo by Nassim Benchaabane 
UPDATED at 11 a.m. Friday with name of victim 
ST. LOUIS • A man from Cape Girardeau was fatally shot Thursday night in the West End neighborhood, police said. 
Travis Scales, 35, of Cape Girardeau, was found lying in the in the 5500 block of Cates Avenue at about 10:30 p.m. Thursday, police said. Scales had been shot multiple times and was pronounced dead at the scene. 
Police say they have no suspects in Scales' death. The shooting was in a residential block with several vacant and dilapidated buildings.
